NAME
lxcu-start -- Start a linux container.
SYNOPSIS
lxcu-start {-h|-V|-n CONTAINER_NAME}
lxcu-start [OPTIONS]
DESCRIPTION
This script starts a linux container. If the bridge key / value pair is set in
sysconfdir/lxcu.conf then the script will check if the bridge is 'UP', if so it
will use a config using that bridge. This feature is particularly useful for
laptops which can have a hard-wired ethernet connection.
OPTIONS
-h, --help Display this help information

-n, --name 'container name'

-V, --version Print script version information
EXIT STATUS
0 - Success

1 - General failure

64 - Error in command line
FILES
lxcu.conf  The script reads the configuration file to set default values.
